1 (2) THE PORTION OF THE DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEES,
2 SURCHARGES, OR EXCISE TAXES PAID TO THE COUNTY BY LEGISLATIVE,
3 COUNCILMANIC, OR COMMISSIONER DISTRICT IN WHICH THE CONSTRUCTION OR
4 DEVELOPMENT PROJECT THAT IS SUBJECT TO THE FEE, SURCHARGE, OR TAX IS
5 LOCATED; AND
6 (3) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED BY SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, THE
7 PORTION OF DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEES, SURCHARGES, OR EXCISE TAXES USED TO
8 FUND CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROJECTS IN THE LEGISLATIVE, COUNCILMANIC, OR
9 COMMISSIONER DISTRICT THAT ARE RELATED TO TRANSPORTATION
10 IMPROVEMENTS OR MAINTENANCE, SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION OR MAINTENANCE, OR
11 ANY OTHER CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROJECT THAT RECEIVED FUNDING FROM
12 DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEES, SURCHARGES, OR EXCISE TAXES.
13 (C) IF THE FUNDING UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(3) OF THIS SECTION IS
14 COLLECTED UNDER SUBTITLE 8 OF THIS TITLE, THE REPORT MAY EXCLUDE THE
15 INFORMATION OTHERWISE REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(3) OF THIS SECTION.
16 (D) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, A COUNTY
17 SHALL MAKE THE REPORT PUBLICLY AVAILABLE ON THE COUNTY’S WEBSITE.
18 (2) A COUNTY THAT DOES NOT MAINTAIN A WEBSITE SHALL MAKE
19 THE REPORT PUBLICLY AVAILABLE BY OTHER REASONABLE MEANS.
20 (3) A COUNTY MAY SUBMIT THE REPORT AS PART OF ANOTHER
21 REPORT REQUIRED UNDER THIS ARTICLE.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
23 October 1, 2025.

